    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1880-04-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1880-04-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="271" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d271">
                <head>No. 271.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Evarts</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">White</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-04-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 14,
                            1880</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 96.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                        dispatch No. 93 of the 4th ultimo, communicating the request of the
                        committee of the International Fishery Exhibition at Berlin, for the
                        appointment of one or two persons experienced in fishery matters as members
                        of an international jury which will be charged with reporting on the
                        exhibits and awarding the prizes.</p>
                <p>In reply I have to inform you that this Department has decided to designate
                        Deputy Commissioner George Brown Goode and Mr. Fred. <pb facs="0523" n="423" xml:id="pg_423"/> Mather, of his staff, to serve in the capacity
                        indicated, and you will accordingly notify the proper authorities of the
                        exhibition to that effect, and also inform the gentlemen just named of their
                        designation.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WM. M. EVARTS..</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
